\b FAQS\cf0\b0\f2\fs24\par
\cf1\i\f0\fs20 Help, I can't see anything in the smithing menu!\cf0\i0\f2\fs24\par
\cf3\f0\fs20 Remember, you need to \i take the perks\i0  to be able to build the associated items. You can't build cores without the Enchanting perks, you can't build bots without the Smithing perks.\cf0\f2\fs24\par
\par
\cf1\i\f0\fs20 I'm using another mod that alters the Smithing perk tree, how can I take the perks?\cf0\i0\f2\fs24\par
\cf3\f0\fs20 Try shuffling around the load order of your mods- the latest mod that changes the perks will be the one that displays its alterations. You'll still have the perks from both mods whatever order they're in. Otherwise, use\cf4  'Find \ldblquote PERKNAME\rdblquote  4'\cf3  in the console, and \cf4 'AddPerk PERKNUMBER'\cf3  to add them manually.\cf0\f2\fs24\par
\cf3\f0\fs20\par
\cf1\i One of my bots won't fight!\cf0\i0\f2\fs24\par
\cf3\f0\fs20 This occasionally happens if you go through a door with your weapon drawn, and is an apparently unfixable bug in Skyrim's AI. To fix it, use \cf2\i Order Dwemer Constructs\i0  \cf3 whilst viewing the affected bot and select 'Reset'.\cf0\f2\fs24\par
\cf1\i\f0\fs20\par
I can't loot a downed bot/I don't get the repair menu on downed bots!\cf0\i0\f2\fs24\par
\cf3\f0\fs20 Sometimes, downed bots won't actually open when you select loot. To fix this, enter sneak mode and try again. Conversely, if you don't get the repair menu then unsneak.\cf0\f2\fs24\par
\cf1\i\f0\fs20\par
How do I remove or reduce the magicka drain?\cf0\i0\f2\fs24\par
\cf3\f0\fs20 The drain per 'tier' is stored in a global variable. Search for the ID using 'Help \cf5 a0aDwGlobalUpkeep\cf3 ' in the console, then use \cf5 [ID].SetValue(newValue)\cf3  to change it. The default is 30.\cf0\f2\fs24\par
\cf3\f0\fs20\par
\cf1\i Is there a maximum number of constructs I can have following me at once?\cf0\i0\f2\fs24\par
\cf3\b\f0\fs28 128\b0 . \fs20 You do not need more than this. To repeat, this is how many you can have \i following you\i0 - you can build any number.\cf0\f2\fs24\par
\cf3\f0\fs20\par
\cf1\i Do I need to be able to create the right core for it to be able to forge a Construct?\cf0\i0\f2\fs24\par
\cf3\f0\fs20 Nope. With only Dwemer Enchanting you can build Centurions, if you have Numidium Scholar and a spare Centurion Dynamo Core. \cf0\f2\fs24\par
\cf3\f0\fs20\par
\cf1\i How many upgrades can a Construct have?\cf0\i0\f2\fs24\par
\cf3\f0\fs20 One \b Components \b0 and one special \b Core\b0 . You'll have to choose between inventory and stronger steam breath, or armour-piercing crossbow bolts.\cf0\f2\fs24\par
